14 ** MK60DN256ZVMD10
15 **
16 ** Compilers: ARM Compiler
17 ** Freescale C/C++ for Embedded ARM
18 ** GNU C Compiler
19 ** IAR ANSI C/C++ Compiler for ARM
20 **
21 ** Reference manual: K60P144M100SF2RM, Rev. 5, 8 May 2011
22 ** Version: rev. 1.2, 2011-09-08
23 **
24 ** Abstract:
25 ** CMSIS Peripheral Access Layer for MK60DZ10
26 **
27 ** Copyright: 1997 - 2011 Freescale Semiconductor, Inc. All Rights Reserved.
28 **
29 ** http: www.freescale.com
30 ** mail: support@freescale.com
31 **
32 ** Revisions:
33 ** - rev. 1.0 (2011-06-10)
34 ** Initial version.
35 ** Changes with respect to the previous MK60NxxxMD100 header file:
36 ** RTC - CCR register removed. Replaced by IER register.
37 ** CRC - added CTRLHU register for 8-bit access to the CTRL register.
38 ** FB - bit FB_CSCR_EXALE renamed to FB_CSCR_EXTS.
39 ** SIM - bit group FSIZE in SIM_FCFG1 split into groups PFSIZE and NVMSIZE.
40 ** I2S - bit SSIEN in I2S_CR register renamed to I2SEN.
41 ** SDHC - bit VOLTSEL in SDHC_VENDOR register removed.
42 ** - rev. 1.1 (2011-06-29)
43 ** Order of declarations changed.
44 ** - rev. 1.2 (2011-09-08)
45 ** Cortex_Core_Configuration extended with additional parameters.
46 ** Gap between end of interrupt vector table and flash configuration field filled by default ISR.
47 ** - rev. 1.2-jg (2015-05-18)
48 ** Added BITBAND_REG32, BITBAND_REG16, BITBAND_REG8, BITBAND_REGADDR macros from MK60D10.h.
49 ** Removed BITBAND_REG macro.
50 **
51 ** ###################################################################
52 */

1405 typedef struct {
1406  struct { /* offset: 0x0, array step: 0x100 */
1407  __IO uint32_t PRS;
1408  uint8_t RESERVED_0[12];
1409  __IO uint32_t CRS;
1410  uint8_t RESERVED_1[236];
1411  } SLAVE[5];
1412  uint8_t RESERVED_0[768];
1413  __IO uint32_t MGPCR0;
1414  uint8_t RESERVED_1[252];
1415  __IO uint32_t MGPCR1;
1416  uint8_t RESERVED_2[252];
1417  __IO uint32_t MGPCR2;
1418  uint8_t RESERVED_3[252];
1419  __IO uint32_t MGPCR3;
1420  uint8_t RESERVED_4[252];
1421  __IO uint32_t MGPCR4;
1422  uint8_t RESERVED_5[252];
1423  __IO uint32_t MGPCR5;
1424 } AXBS_Type;

1429 
1435 /* PRS Bit Fields */
1436 #define AXBS_PRS_M0_MASK 0x7u
1437 #define AXBS_PRS_M0_SHIFT 0
1438 #define AXBS_PRS_M0(x) (((uint32_t)(((uint32_t)(x))<<AXBS_PRS_M0_SHIFT))&AXBS_PRS_M0_MASK)
1439 #define AXBS_PRS_M1_MASK 0x70u
1440 #define AXBS_PRS_M1_SHIFT 4
1441 #define AXBS_PRS_M1(x) (((uint32_t)(((uint32_t)(x))<<AXBS_PRS_M1_SHIFT))&AXBS_PRS_M1_MASK)

1519 typedef struct {
1520  __IO uint32_t MCR;
1521  __IO uint32_t CTRL1;
1522  __IO uint32_t TIMER;
1523  uint8_t RESERVED_0[4];
1524  __IO uint32_t RXMGMASK;
1525  __IO uint32_t RX14MASK;
1526  __IO uint32_t RX15MASK;
1527  __IO uint32_t ECR;
1528  __IO uint32_t ESR1;
1529  __IO uint32_t IMASK2;
1530  __IO uint32_t IMASK1;
1531  __IO uint32_t IFLAG2;
1532  __IO uint32_t IFLAG1;
1533  __IO uint32_t CTRL2;
1534  __I uint32_t ESR2;
1535  uint8_t RESERVED_1[8];
1536  __I uint32_t CRCR;
1537  __IO uint32_t RXFGMASK;
1538  __I uint32_t RXFIR;
1539  uint8_t RESERVED_2[48];
1540  struct { /* offset: 0x80, array step: 0x10 */
1541  __IO uint32_t CS;
1542  __IO uint32_t ID;
1543  __IO uint32_t WORD0;
1544  __IO uint32_t WORD1;
1545  } MB[16];
1546  uint8_t RESERVED_3[1792];
1547  __IO uint32_t RXIMR[16];
1548 } CAN_Type;

7645 /* ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
7646  -- SPI Peripheral Access Layer
7647  ---------------------------------------------------------------------------- */
7648 
7655 typedef struct {
7656  __IO uint32_t MCR;
7657  uint8_t RESERVED_0[4];
7658  __IO uint32_t TCR;
7659  union { /* offset: 0xC */
7660  __IO uint32_t CTAR[2];
7661  __IO uint32_t CTAR_SLAVE[1];
7662  };
7663  uint8_t RESERVED_1[24];
7664  __IO uint32_t SR;
7665  __IO uint32_t RSER;
7666  union { /* offset: 0x34 */
7667  __IO uint32_t PUSHR;
7668  __IO uint32_t PUSHR_SLAVE;
7669  };
7670  __I uint32_t POPR;
7671  __I uint32_t TXFR0;
7672  __I uint32_t TXFR1;
7673  __I uint32_t TXFR2;
7674  __I uint32_t TXFR3;
7675  uint8_t RESERVED_2[48];
7676  __I uint32_t RXFR0;
7677  __I uint32_t RXFR1;
7678  __I uint32_t RXFR2;
7679  __I uint32_t RXFR3;
7680 } SPI_Type;
